column23: I’m slowly getting better

It's been an interesting and revealing journey. Dropping my safety behaviour of avoiding eye contact with others hasn't been as scary as I thought. Making eye contact with others is making me feel more connected with them and also seems to calm me down. I didn't expect that.  I'm starting to look forward to spending time with other people. Maybe I'm not as much of an introvert as I thought!
